@database "Compress Guide"
@author "Heiko Schr÷der"
@$VER: 3.0 (Release 3)
@wordwrap

@node main "Compress V3.0"
                               @{" < Table of Contents " link "Macro-Package.guide/Main"}

@{fg shine}Benefits:@{fg text}
   The macro can be used to archive complex documents, especially if you don't
   want to change them anymore...
   When ╗Final Writer½ saves a document the file often gets very big and
   it wastes a lot of HD space. Even if there is only a little text in the
   document. If you save a blank document it blows up to 21.804 bytes and
   that's without any written text!

   This macro offers
      - automatic LHA/LZX-compression while saving a document.
      - automatic opening of LHA/LZX-compressed documents.

@{fg shine}Requirements:@{fg text}
 a] You need both (or at least one) of these compression programs:

                       Lha (® Stefan Boberg)
                       Lzx (® Data Compression Technologies)

    They should be placed in your C: drawer.
    You also need the original Workbench-command Delete (® Commodore, Inc.).
    
    Because of the copyright these programs are not included with this package.

 b] LZX needs at least 500kB available memory (RAM) to process the compression!


@{fg shine}Using the @{"macro" system "Sys:Utilities/Multiview Compress.iff"}:@{fg text}

   Filename:
      The name of the document (along with its path) is displayed here.

   @{fg fill}M@{fg text}ode:
      If you have both the compression utilities you can decide which 
      compression program you want to use, whether Lha or Lzx.
      Otherwise the only program that the macro has found in the C: drawer 
      will be used.

   @{fg fill}D@{fg text}elete Original:
      If this option is checked the original document will be deleted after
      the compression. This means only the compressed document will be saved.
      Otherwise you get an uncompressed-backup file.

   Do@{fg fill}c@{fg text} Adjustments:
      Final Writer offers the possibility to save document adjustments along
      with the document. If you don't want to give the document away can be
      useful not to use this feature. You will save up to 20kB per document!

                     - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 

   @{fg fill}O@{fg text}pen
      A requester will appear that only shows files matching #?.fwlha or
      #?.fwlzx. You can now select a file. The document will then automa-
      tically be decompressed and opened. 

   @{fg fill}S@{fg text}ave
      Your document will be compressed and saved and the extension #?.fwlha
      or #?.fwlzx will be added. If your document doesn't have a name yet you
      are asked to enter one.

   Save @{fg fill}A@{fg text}s
      That's the common other method for saving a document. You are asked
      for a new document name.

   @{fg fill}ESC@{fg text} or closing window
      Terminates the macro.

@endnode
